<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for statement’s third clause modifies more than the single loop counter. The loop uses len as the loop counter (tested in the second clause and decremented in the third), but the third clause also updates dest and ptr (dest += sizeof(int), ptr += sizeof(int)). MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 requires the third clause to modify only the loop counter (and only one loop counter shall be present). Therefore this fragment violates Rule 14.2.
</scenario>

